### ip-lookup-api — local requests (VS Code REST Client / JetBrains HTTP Client)
### Server: bun dev  (default port 3000, or set PORT)
### Set IP_LOOKUP_API_KEY in the environment; use the same value below:
@apiKey = your-secret-key-here

### GeoIP for an IP (query parameter ip)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/v1/ip-lookup?ip=145.255.49.45
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}

###

### GeoIP for another IP (IPv6 example)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/v1/ip-lookup?ip=2001:4860:4860::8888
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}

###

### GeoIP for the calling client (socket IP; behind a proxy use headers below)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/v1/ip-lookup/me
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}

###

### Same as /me but simulate client IP (when your proxy sets X-Forwarded-For)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/v1/ip-lookup/me
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
X-Forwarded-For: 203.0.113.42

###

### Optional: Cloudflare / other edge headers
GET http://localhost:3000/api/v1/ip-lookup/me
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
CF-Connecting-IP: 198.51.100.7
